# =====================================================================
# abc-os-community — Env vars template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is the SOURCE OF TRUTH for which env vars the app expects.
# It is committed to git on purpose (.env.example, no real values).
# Real values are NEVER written here (Test Key Pragma).
#
# Doctrine reference: ADR-ABCOS-001 D7 + 04_vercel/AGENTS.md W2
# (C:/Users/amado/ASpace_OS_V2/10_Tech_OS/11_Infra_13th_Doctor/06_MCP_Mastery/04_vercel/AGENTS.md)
# =====================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3-scope rule (Vercel)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Vercel has 3 env scopes: development, preview, production. The SAME
# var name can hold 3 different values. For NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars used by
# the browser bundle, we want ONE value across all 3 scopes so the app
# behaves identically in dev, preview deploys, and prod.
#
# Wiring pattern: apply-vercel-env.ps1 (scripts/apply-vercel-env.ps1)
# calls mcp__vercel__update_env_variable x 3 in parallel, then
# re-verifies with list_env_variables (Vercel sometimes silently drops
# the target array on PATCH).
#
# NEVER set SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY in any Vercel env. The dashboard
# reads with anon + RLS. Write ops use the VPS-side aspace_admin role
# (per ADR-SUPABASE-001 D2). The line below is commented out as a
# permanent guard rail.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Public — sent to the browser (NEXT_PUBLIC_* is exposed by Next.js)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://supabase.kalybana.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<from A0 via Test Key Pragma>

# Server-only — NEVER set in Vercel (used only on VPS via aspace_admin)
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test Key Pragma — how real values reach Vercel
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Real anon keys NEVER live in this file, in .env.local, in .json, or
# in any git-tracked file. The flow is:
#
#   1. A0 pastes the anon key in chat with explicit intent ("teste ca").
#   2. Agent: [Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable(
#                  'ASPACE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY', '<key>', 'User')
#   3. Agent: pwsh ./scripts/apply-vercel-env.ps1 `
#                  -Key NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY `
#                  -Value $env:ASPACE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#   4. Agent: re-verifies via mcp__vercel__list_env_variables.
#   5. A0: revokes + recreates the key in Supabase dashboard.
#   6. A0: optionally re-pastes the new key for a clean rotation, or
#          resets $env:ASPACE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY directly.
#
# .env.local on the dev box is allowed (gitignored via .gitignore:34)
# but the Vercel side is ALWAYS set through the script, never by hand.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
